Credit Agricole Prepares to Eliminate 2,000 Jobs, Le Figaro Says

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-12-13T21:58:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-13/credit-agricole-prepares-to-eliminate-2-000-jobs-le-figaro-says.html
Credit Agricole SA (ACA)  is planning to
eliminate about 2,000 jobs, Le Figaro reported, citing a person
with knowledge of the matter. Most of the jobs will go at the
lender’s investment bank unit CIB, where 1,500 jobs will be cut,
the newspaper said.  Messages left on the voicemail of Credit Agricole’s press
office outside office hours today weren’t immediately answered.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 